trans-unit.source: This document depicts Azure ML Recommendations APIs.
trans-unit.target: This document depicts Azure ML Recommendations APIs.

trans-unit.source: This document is an API reference.
trans-unit.target: This document is an API reference.

trans-unit.source: You should start with the “Azure ML Recommendation – Quick Start” document.
trans-unit.target: You should start with the “Azure ML Recommendation – Quick Start” document.

trans-unit.source: Azure ML Recommendations API can be divided into 8 groups:
trans-unit.target: Azure ML Recommendations API can be divided into 8 groups:

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Model Basic<html></html> – APIs that enable you to do the basic operations on model (e.g. create, update and delete a model).
trans-unit.target: <html></html>Model Basic<html></html> – APIs that enable you to do the basic operations on model (e.g. create, update and delete a model).

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Model Advanced<html></html> – APIs that enable you to get advanced data insights on the model
trans-unit.target: <html></html>Model Advanced<html></html> – APIs that enable you to get advanced data insights on the model

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Model Business Rules<html></html> – APIs that enables you to manage business rules on the model recommendation results.
trans-unit.target: <html></html>Model Business Rules<html></html> – APIs that enables you to manage business rules on the model recommendation results.

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Catalog<html></html> – APIs that enable you to do basic operations on a model catalog.
trans-unit.target: <html></html>Catalog<html></html> – APIs that enable you to do basic operations on a model catalog.

trans-unit.source: A catalog contains Meta data information on the items of the usage data.
trans-unit.target: A catalog contains Meta data information on the items of the usage data.

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Usage Data<html></html> – APIs that enable you to do basic operations on the model usage data. Usage data in the basic form consist on rows that include pairs of <html></html>,<html></html>
trans-unit.target: <html></html>Usage Data<html></html> – APIs that enable you to do basic operations on the model usage data. Usage data in the basic form consist on rows that include pairs of <html></html>,<html></html>

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Build<html></html> – APIs that enable to trigger a model build and do basic operation that are related to this build.
trans-unit.target: <html></html>Build<html></html> – APIs that enable to trigger a model build and do basic operation that are related to this build.

trans-unit.source: You can trigger a model build once you have valuable usage data.
trans-unit.target: You can trigger a model build once you have valuable usage data.

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Recommendation<html></html> – Once the build of a model ends you can consume recommendations using these APIs.
trans-unit.target: <html></html>Recommendation<html></html> – Once the build of a model ends you can consume recommendations using these APIs.

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Notifications<html></html> – Enables you to receive notifications on problems related to your API operations (e.g. you are reporting usage data via Data Acquisition and most of the events processing are failing.
trans-unit.target: <html></html>Notifications<html></html> – Enables you to receive notifications on problems related to your API operations (e.g. you are reporting usage data via Data Acquisition and most of the events processing are failing.

trans-unit.source: An error notification will be raised)
trans-unit.target: An error notification will be raised)

trans-unit.source: Maximum number of models per subscription: 10
trans-unit.target: Maximum number of models per subscription: 10

trans-unit.source: Maximum number of items that a catalog can hold: 100,000
trans-unit.target: Maximum number of items that a catalog can hold: 100,000

trans-unit.source: The maximum amount of usage points that are kept is ~5,000,000.
trans-unit.target: The maximum amount of usage points that are kept is ~5,000,000.

trans-unit.source: The oldest will be deleted if new ones will be uploaded or reported.
trans-unit.target: The oldest will be deleted if new ones will be uploaded or reported.

trans-unit.source: Maximum size of data can be sent in POST (e.g. Import catalog data, import usage data) is 200MB
trans-unit.target: Maximum size of data can be sent in POST (e.g. Import catalog data, import usage data) is 200MB

trans-unit.source: The number of transactions per second for a recommendation model build that is not active is ~2TPS, only recommendation model build that is active can hold up to 20TPS
trans-unit.target: The number of transactions per second for a recommendation model build that is not active is ~2TPS, only recommendation model build that is active can hold up to 20TPS

trans-unit.source: <html></html>Active Build Id<html></html> – Every build for every model has a “build id”. The active “build id” is the first successfully build of every new model. Once you have an active build Id and you do additional builds for the same model you need to explicit set it as the default build id if you want to. When you consume recommendations, if you do not specify the build id that you want to use the default one will be used automatically.<html></html>

When you consume recommendations, if you do not specify the build id that you want to use the default one will be used automatically.<html></html>

trans-unit.source: <html></html>The number of iterations the model performs is reflected by the overall compute time and the model accuracy.The higher the number - the better accuracy you will get, but the compute time will take longer.<html></html>
trans-unit.target: <html></html>The number of iterations the model performs is reflected by the overall compute time and the model accuracy.The higher the number - the better accuracy you will get, but the compute time will take longer.<html></html>

trans-unit.source: <html></html>The number of dimensions relates to the number of 'features' the model will try to find within your data.Increasing the number of dimensions will allow better fine tuning of the results into smaller clusters.However, too many dimensions will prevent the model from finding correlations between items.<html></html>
trans-unit.target: <html></html>The number of dimensions relates to the number of 'features' the model will try to find within your data.Increasing the number of dimensions will allow better fine tuning of the results into smaller clusters.However, too many dimensions will prevent the model from finding correlations between items.<html></html>

trans-unit.source: <html></html>You can control the minimum number of appearances which an item is not included in the model.The higher the threshold, the better results you'll get from the model.However, if the threshold is too high, you may end up with not enough items to be of use for you.<html></html>
trans-unit.target: <html></html>You can control the minimum number of appearances which an item is not included in the model.The higher the threshold, the better results you'll get from the model.However, if the threshold is too high, you may end up with not enough items to be of use for you.<html></html>

trans-unit.source: <html></html>You can control the minimum number of appearances which a user is not included in the model.The higher the threshold, the better results you'll get from the model.However, if the threshold is too high, you may end up with not enough items to be of use for you, or no recommendations for a specific user.<html></html>
trans-unit.target: <html></html>You can control the minimum number of appearances which a user is not included in the model.The higher the threshold, the better results you'll get from the model.However, if the threshold is too high, you may end up with not enough items to be of use for you, or no recommendations for a specific user.<html></html>

trans-unit.source: Azure ML Recommendations creates notification when there are persistent errors that happen in the system.
trans-unit.target: Azure ML Recommendations creates notification when there are persistent errors that happen in the system.

trans-unit.source: Build failure – this notification is triggered for every build failure.
trans-unit.target: Build failure – this notification is triggered for every build failure.

trans-unit.source: Data Acquisition processing failure - this notification is triggered when we have more than 100 errors in the last 5 minutes in the processing of usage events per model.
trans-unit.target: Data Acquisition processing failure - this notification is triggered when we have more than 100 errors in the last 5 minutes in the processing of usage events per model.

trans-unit.source: Recommendation consumption failure - this notification is triggered when we have more than 100 errors in the last 5 minutes in the processing of recommendation requests per model.
trans-unit.target: Recommendation consumption failure - this notification is triggered when we have more than 100 errors in the last 5 minutes in the processing of recommendation requests per model.
